<h1>Aloo Fry Recipe</h1> 
<p>Now we are going to make an Aloo Recvipe</p> 
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>1/2 kg Aloo</li>
<li>250 grm oil</li>
<li>Salt on need basis</li>
<li>Green chilli on need basis</li>
<li> Two Spoon Gram Masala</li>
<li>3 Cups Water</li>
<li>Dhaniya on need basis</li>
<li>Tomato 200 grm</li>
<li>Onion 200 grm</li>
</ul>
</body>
<h3>Method</h3>
<ol>
<li>First of  all wash the aloo properly and cut in small pieces</li>
<li>cut or grind the onion, tomato, Dhaniya and green Chilli</li>
<li>put the frypan on burned and put oil in it</li>
<li>put the paste of onion, tomato etc in it</li>
<li>put the Gram masala, salt etc in it and mix it properly</li>
<li>Then put the aloo in the frypan and mix it with the paste</li>
<li>put the water in it and keep it for 20 x minutes on burner</li>
<li>Now my aloo recipe is redy to eat</li>
</ol>